The paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of preference relations and consistency conditions, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The concept of self-stability is related to stability and equilibrium, which are studied in both computer science (cs.DS) and social choice theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes a new class of social choice functions, which could be of interest to researchers in social informatics (cs.SI).
